-- Itochu, Abengoa to Build Solar Power Plants in Spain, Invest $500 Million
-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 2010-12-20T09:42:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/itochu-abengoa-to-build-solar-power-plants-in-spain-invest-500-million.html
Itochu Corp. will join a solar power
project in Spain with Abengoa Solar SA.  The Japanese trading company will take a 30 percent stake
in the 500 million euro ($658 million) project, in which the
companies will own two 50-megawatt solar-thermal plants in
Logrosan, Spain.  The plants are expected to start operation in 2012, Itochu
said today in a release on its website.  Shares in  Abengoa SA , the parent company, rose 0.3 percent
to 17.82 euros as of 10:28 a.m. in Madrid trading, compared with
a 0.1 percent gain in the 38-member Bloomberg Global Leaders
Solar Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
